Basic command related to docker images
docker images => To check avaliable images.
docker ps => To list of running container
docker search centos => To search images
docker pull centos => To download images
docker run --name some-name -d  => To run container in deamon mode
docker exec -it cname /bin/bash => login 
docker logs cname => To check the logs
docker rm cname => To remove
docker inspect cname => for details
docker stop cname => stop container

docker top cname => to check process (polkitd)
docker attach cname => only when /bin/bash avalible
docker run -it -p 8080:8080 --name myjenkin -d jenkins/jenkins  <<jenkins

ps -aux to check process 

docker stats cname => To check ram

docker commit con1 centos:v1
docker run -it -name con2 centos:v1
docker run -it --name demo centos:latest

Volume attached
docker run -d -v /v1:/var/lib/mysql --name db -e MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD=redhat mariadb

We can run container in two mode
a) root mode
b) deamon mode
=================================

